Family: egcd_bezout

Asserts the Bezout identity for a software implementation of the
extended Euclidean algorithm: for two signed k-bit inputs (a, b),
the algorithm returns (g, x, y) with x*a + y*b == g, where g is
the (non-negative) gcd of a and b.

The implementation iterates a fixed number of steps (4*k + 4) of
the classical eGCD recurrence in 4*k-bit signed arithmetic. The
iteration count is well above the worst-case Fibonacci bound, so
the algorithm always terminates with the correct result; the
property states this end-to-end.

Source: this is the Bezout-soundness lemma 'eGCD_bezout' from the
Cryptol model documenting the strides bitvector abstract domain,
flattened to pure QF_BV by sign-extending inputs to 4*k bits.

The k = 8 variant has signed inputs of k bits and runs eGCD in
4*k bits with 4*k + 4 unrolled iterations. Solver difficulty grows
quickly with k because the unrolled body contains O(k) chained
nonlinear bitvector multiplications and subtractions.
